" /></a><a href="x41339.xml"><img alt="Courses" height="65" onmouseout="this.src='Images/Admin_Offices/Online Learning/Concurrent Enrollment/CE710TopMenu_r1_c2_s1.jpg';" onmouseover="this.src='Images/Admin_Offices/Online Learning/Concurrent Enrollment/CE710TopMenu_r1_c2_s2.jpg';" src="Images/Admin_Offices/Online Learning/Concurrent Enrollment/CE710TopMenu_r1_c2_s1.jpg" style="float: left;" width="181" /></a><a href="x42290.xml"><img alt="Apply" height="65" src="Images/Admin_Offices/Online Learning/Concurrent Enrollment/CE710TopMenu_r1_c3_s2.jpg" style="float: left;" width="183" /></a> <a href="x41341.xml"><img alt="Registration" height="65" onmouseout="this.src='Images/Admin_Offices/Online Learning/Concurrent Enrollment/CE710TopMenu_r1_c4_s1.jpg';" onmouseover="this.src='Images/Admin_Offices/Online Learning/Concurrent Enrollment/CE710TopMenu_r1_c4_s2.jpg';" src="Images/Admin_Offices/Online Learning/Concurrent Enrollment/CE710TopMenu_r1_c4_s1.jpg" style="float: left;" width="173" /></a> <img alt="Libary Shot" height="248" src="Images/Admin_Offices/Online Learning/Concurrent Enrollment/Libary shot 2.jpg" width="710" />&nbsp;<img alt="Apply Icon" height="60" src="Images/Admin_Offices/Online Learning/Concurrent Enrollment/Apply-Title.gif" title="Apply Icon" width="540" /><br />High school students desiring to take concurrent enrollment classes must be enrolled in a high school or home school program.</p>
<div><strong>Required Application Materials</strong></div>
<div>
<ul>
<li>Part 1: Student Information</li>
<li>Part 2: School Selection</li>
<li>Part 3: Ecclesiastical Endorsement</li>
<li>$35 application fee</li>
<li>BYU-Idaho Concurrent Enrollment Voucher</li>
<li>High school/home school transcript</li>
</ul>
</div>
<div></div>
<div>Students applying for on-campus Concurrent Enrollment classes have the following additional requirements:</div>
<div>
<ul>
<li>The applicant must have a minimum cumulative 3.0 high school GPA</li>
<li>If home schooled, submit an ACT score of 16 or higher</li>
</ul>
</div>
<div></div>
<div><strong>Restrictions:</strong></div>
<div>
<ul>
<li>Online Concurrent Enrollment students should be in their junior or senior year of high school.</li>
<li>On-campus concurrent enrollment students must have completed their junior year of high school.</li>
<li>Concurrent Enrollment students are limited to six credit hours per semester.</li>
<li>BYU-Idaho Student Housing is not available to Concurrent Enrollment students.</li>
<li>Students may not take online and on-campus Concurrent Enrollment classes simultaneously.</li>
<li>If you want to change from one Concurrent Enrollment type to another, you must reapply.</li>
</ul>
</div>
<div></div>
<div>Application processing time: 1 week</div>
<div>Print the BYU-Idaho <a href="Documents/Admin_Offices/Admissions/onlineConcEnr.pdf" title="Online Concurrent Enrollment Voucher">Online Concurrent Enrollment Voucher</a> (PDF)</div>
<div>Print the BYU-Idaho <a href="Documents/Admin_Offices/Admissions/onCampusConcEnr.pdf" title="On-Campus Concurrent Enrollment Voucher">On-campus Concurrent Enrollment Voucher</a> (PDF)</div>
<div></div>
<div>To fill out Parts 1, 2, and 3 of the application, visit <a class="extLink" href="http://besmart.com" title="BeSmart.com" target="_blank">www.besmart.com</a>.</div>
<div></div>
<br />
